{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_17","type":"agent_message","text":"I’ve confirmed the driver exposes `MongoClientOptions.Builder.alwaysUseMBeans(boolean)`, and the failure happens while it tries to register JMX connection-pool listeners during `MongoClient` construction. Next I’m verifying that turning that off removes the JMX path cleanly, rather than patching broad JDK management metadata for a test that doesn’t need JMX to validate Morphia."}}
