{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_31","type":"agent_message","text":"The root cause is clearer now: this Mongo 3.4 driver unconditionally installs `JMXConnectionPoolListener` inside `Mongo.createCluster(...)`, so every `MongoClient` creation hits platform MBean registration in native. This is not tied to the Morphia test logic itself; I’m checking existing metadata patterns for MXBeans to see whether the correct fix is to expand the Mongo driver metadata for this JMX path, rather than weakening the test."}}
